      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Yousuf Karsh (1908-2002) was an Armenian-Canadian portrait photographer, recognized by  Time magazine and the Metropolitan Museum of Art as one of the great portrait photographers of the 20th century.</p><p>Alfred Carl Fuller (1885-1973) was a Canadian-American businessman and founder of the Fuller Brush Company (1906).  At the time this photograph was taken, he was chairman of the board.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Yousuf Karsh Photograph of Alfred Fuller</emph> consists of a single photograph, a formal portrait of Alfred C. Fuller of the Fuller Brush Company.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
